  "analysis": "This task implements counted sub-structure collections (e.g., `sub bolts : List<Bolt>`) with count constraints that trigger schema re-elaboration. The implementation spans 5 modules:\n\n1. **Grammar (tree-sitter-reify)**: The current `sub_declaration` rule only supports `sub name = StructName<TypeArgs>(args)`. The spec requires `sub name : List<StructName>` form. We need to extend the grammar rule to support a collection form using `choice()` \u2014 the existing `=` instantiation form plus a new `:` collection-type form.\n\n2. **Syntax (reify-syntax)**: `SubDecl` needs an `is_collection: bool` field. The parser's `lower_sub()` must detect the collection form (when the grammar produces a node with the colon/List form) and set `is_collection=true`, extracting the element type name as structure_name.\n\n3. **Compiler (reify-compiler)**: `SubComponentDecl` needs `is_collection: bool` and `count_cell: Option<ValueCellId>`. When `is_collection` is true, the compiler must create a synthetic count ValueCell (e.g., `S.__count_bolts`, type Int, Let kind) and recognize `constraint bolts.count == expr` as structure-controlling (adding the count cell to `structure_controlling`). The count cell's expression comes from the constraint RHS.\n\n4. **Eval graph (reify-eval/graph.rs)**: `from_templates()` must handle collection sub-components. If `is_collection` and count is determined (Int(N)), create N scoped instances: `Parent.name[0]`, `Parent.name[1]`, etc. Each instance gets full value cells from the child template. If count is Undef, no instances are created.\n\n5. **Eval engine (reify-eval/lib.rs)**: Count re-elaboration \u2014 when the count ValueCell's value changes, trigger graph topology change: add/remove instances to match new count. This follows the existing guard re-elaboration pattern.\n\n**Review Fix Analysis (steps 21-26):**\n\n- **Issue 1 (unnecessary_full_collection_rebuild)**: The count-change re-elaboration at lib.rs:1625-1630 rebuilds the entire ValueMap O(V_total) on every count change. PersistentMap already has remove(), but ValueMap doesn't expose it. Fix: add ValueMap::remove() and replace the full rebuild with surgical removal of stale instance entries O(count_diff \u00d7 child_cells).\n\n- **Issues 2+4 (incorrect_type_annotation + missing assertion)**: The compiler hardcodes `result_type: Type::Real` at lines 896 and 907 for all indexed collection member accesses regardless of the member's actual type. Fix: extend CompilationScope to store a mapping from (collection_name, member_name) \u2192 Type by looking up already-compiled child templates. Pass `&[TopologyTemplate]` to compile_entity. Use this to resolve the correct member type. The existing test also lacks a result_type assertion.\n\n- **Issue 3 (declaration_order_dependency)**: When `constraint bolts.count == n` appears before `sub bolts : List<Bolt>` in source order, the single-pass member processing can't find the SubComponentDecl to set count_cell (it hasn't been pushed yet). Fix: add a reconciliation sweep after the second pass that backfills count_cell for any unlinked __count_ cells.\n\n**Review Fix Analysis (steps 27-30, blocking issues from second review):**\n\n- **Issue: silent_failure_always_undef** (lines 912-919): Non-literal (dynamic) index access `bolts[n].member` always evaluates to Undef at runtime. The collection base is constructed as `CompiledExpr::literal(Value::Undef, Type::List<StructureRef>)` \u2014 a constant Undef \u2014 rather than a reference to the actual `__list_{name}` cell that the eval engine creates. At eval time, `Undef[n]` \u2192 Undef, then `Undef.member` \u2192 Undef. Fix: Replace `literal(Value::Undef, ...)` with `value_ref(ValueCellId::new(&scope.entity_name, format!(\"__list_{}\", name)), Type::List(...))` so the dynamic index operates on the actual synthetic list cell. Also emit a compiler diagnostic noting dynamic indexing limitation.\n\n- **Issue: missing_compiler_path_for_collection_aggregation** (lines 675-688): Collection sub names are registered in `scope.collection_sub_names` (line 1717) but never in `scope.names`, so using a collection sub as a standalone identifier (`bolts` in `bolts.all(|b| ...)` or `bolts.map(...)`) hits the `ExprKind::Ident` fallback at line 680, emitting 'unresolved name: bolts' and returning Literal(Undef). The step-19 test only passes because it uses the builder API to directly construct a ValueRef to `__list_bolts`, bypassing the compiler. Fix: In the `ExprKind::Ident` handler, after `scope.resolve(name)` returns None, add a fallback check: if `name` is in `scope.collection_sub_names`, return `CompiledExpr::value_ref(ValueCellId::new(&scope.entity_name, format!(\"__list_{}\", name)), Type::List(Box::new(Type::StructureRef(name.clone()))))`. Also add a source-code integration test (not builder API) for `bolts.all(...)` to prevent regression.\n\nKey existing patterns to reuse:\n- Guard re-elaboration pattern (structure_controlling -> dirty check -> re-evaluate)\n- Sub-component scoping pattern (Parent.sub_name -> scoped ValueCellIds)\n- TopologyTemplateBuilder for test construction\n- `.count`, `.map()`, `.all()` method calls already implemented in reify-expr\n- PersistentMap::remove() already exists, just needs ValueMap wrapper\n\nThe `forall b in bolts: predicate` syntax doesn't exist in the grammar; tests will use `.all(|b| predicate)` instead, which is already supported in the expression evaluator.",
